FBIS3-55473 "drsov006_r_94008" FBIS-SOV-94-006 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Jan 1994 Azerbaijan Fighting Locations, Losses Detailed LD1001134794 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1219 GMT 10 Jan 94 LD1001134794 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vadim Byrkin] [Text] Moscow, 10 Jan -- The Azerbaijani Army resumed its offensive along the entire Karabakh front at 0700 [0400 GMT]. ITAR-TASS was told on the telephone by the Nagorno-Karabakh Republic defense army headquarters that the fighting is particularly heavy in the Mardakert Rayon of Nagorno-Karabakh. On Sunday evening the Azerbaijani Army lost over 50 men killed, two tanks, and an APC during its offensive near the village of Magadiz. Karabakh's losses amounted to three killed and five wounded. According to reports received by 1300, the situation on all sectors of the front remains tense and battles are continuing.
